body:
@mklement0 Thanks for the input!

> `[AutomationNull]::Value -is [AutomationNull]  # should be $true`
> but seeing as the former already works with dbnull and nullstring it should probably be doable for automation null as well... Not sure exactly where that would need to be done, but I can take a look in a day or two :)

@vexx32 I suggest you to not work on supporting this in this PR. I'm not really sure we want to do that because it could cause confusion semantically -- `[AutomationNull]::Value` is treated as null in PowerShell (e.g. `[AutomationNull]::Value.GetType()` fails because it's not considered as an object), The current behavior is consistent and makes sense.
